      "When Paul and Barnabas had their sharp falling-out over whether to bring John Mark on a second journey, Paul chose Silas as his new companion instead, and the two set out together through Syria and Cilicia (Acts 15:40-41). In Philippi, the pair were stripped, severely flogged, and thrown in prison after Paul cast a spirit out of a fortune-telling slave girl — and famously kept praying and singing hymns at midnight until an earthquake shook the prison doors open (Acts 16:19-26).",
