      "The elder writing 3 John complains that he wrote to the church, but \"Diotrephes, who likes to put himself first, does not acknowledge our authority.\" Diotrephes refused to welcome traveling missionaries the elder had sent, spread malicious accusations against the elder, and put out of the church anyone who did want to receive them (3 John 1:9-10). The letter gives no further detail on his position or motives — just this brief, unflattering glimpse of a real power struggle in an early local congregation, a rare counterpoint to the New Testament's usual focus on approved leaders.",
