      "Seeing that human wickedness had become great and that 'every intention of the thoughts of his heart was only evil continually,' God resolved to blot out humanity and all land-dwelling creatures with a flood, but found favor with Noah (Genesis 6:5-8, 11-13).",
      "God instructed Noah to build a large ark of gopher wood, coated with pitch inside and out, giving precise dimensions (300 by 50 by 30 cubits) and instructions to bring his family and two of every kind of animal — seven pairs of clean animals — aboard, along with food for all of them (Genesis 6:14-22; 7:1-3).",
      "At age 600, Noah entered the ark with his wife, his three sons (Shem, Ham, and Japheth), and their wives, along with the animals, just before the rain began. The flood came: 'the fountains of the great deep burst forth, and the windows of the heavens were opened,' and rain fell for forty days and nights, with the waters prevailing over the earth for 150 days (Genesis 7:6-24).",
      "God 'remembered Noah,' and the waters gradually receded; the ark came to rest on the mountains of Ararat. Noah sent out a raven and then a dove three times to test whether the waters had subsided, finally releasing all the animals once the ground was dry (Genesis 8:1-19).",
      "Noah built an altar and offered burnt offerings, and God, pleased by the aroma, resolved never again to curse the ground or destroy every living creature in this way, establishing the seasons as a fixed order (Genesis 8:20-22). God then made a covenant with Noah and 'every living creature,' setting the rainbow as its sign (Genesis 9:1-17).",
      "After the flood, Noah became a man of the soil and planted a vineyard. He drank of its wine, became drunk, and lay uncovered in his tent; his son Ham 'saw the nakedness of his father' and told his brothers, who covered Noah without looking. On waking, Noah pronounced a curse on Ham's son Canaan and blessings on Shem and Japheth — a passage later badly misused historically to justify racial slavery, though it names Canaan, not any racial group (Genesis 9:20-27).",
